comments/data/4/message:
Pluto is not the prevailing object within its orbit. While it is the largest discovered dwarf planet, it no longer fits the description due to the discovery of the Kuiper belt. A planet must:
1. Be large enough to be a sphere
2. Orbit the sun
3. Have cleared its neighborhood orbit of objects of similar size.
Pluto does 2 out of 3, and that's not to bad. In my opinion the downgrade from smallest planet to largest dwarf planet isn't to bad.

comments/data/1/message: First time I ever bought weed I didn't know where to hide it sooo I just left it in my car in like a secret compartment in the back of my car. I go back later in the day to get it and it wasn't there. Instead it was replaced by my dad's business card with the words "gotcha" written on it.
comments/data/2/message: When I was in grade 3, we were doing an art project, and a girl left her ring on the teachers desk so it wouldnt get dirty. Well, I guess I liked it enough-I took it. At the end of the project, when they noticed it was gone, the teacher said-"no-ones leaving this room until we find that ring!" We started walking around the classroom-the whole class. I don't know how many seconds/minutes elapsed before I had the great idea to throw it on the floor and proclaim..."there it is!" What I didn't realize in my 8 short years is how noisy a small ring can be, getting tossed onto a wood floor. Busted! This was very hard to confess, and I haven't taken anything since this very low day in my life. Wow, do I feel better. lol
